item.title: Jagex deobfuscator
item.dc:creator: @moparisthebest Moparisthebest
item.description:
@moparisthebest wrote:

Hate to keep annoying you, but I still have a problem:

mopar@linux-laptop:~/rsdev/rs/rsCURRENT_DEOB_SRC$ javac *.java
client.java:1331: > expected
            aBoolean2628 = <no variable> == 0;
                              ^
client.java:1331: illegal start of expression
            aBoolean2628 = <no variable> == 0;
                               ^
client.java:1331: illegal start of expression
            aBoolean2628 = <no variable> == 0;
                                         ^
3 errors

I get that with and without applying your notremover transform, also I tried your pre-compiled deob.jar and one that I compiled myself from the source you posted. My run.xml and rs2zkm.txt is the same as yours with the exception of the names, and here is the script I wrote to use:

#!/bin/sh

# usage:
# deob file_to_deob deob_bin_location deob_src_location
deob () {
cp $1 ./todeob.jar
# deob file
java -cp .:..:../lib/bcel.jar:../lib/jdom.jar:../lib/regexp.jar:../lib/deob.jar org.saev.deob.Main apply ../run.xml
# rename with ZKM
java -cp .:..:../lib/zkm.jar ZKM ../rs2zkm.txt
mkdir temp
cd temp
mv ../*.txt .
jar xf ../tmpdeob.jar
jad -sjava *.class
badclass=$(grep -l 'goto' *.java | cut -f1 -d'.')
rm $badclass.java
jar cf ../tmpdeobsrc.jar *.java *.txt $badclass.class
cd ..
# save them both to specified location
mv ./tmpdeob.jar $2
mv ./tmpdeobsrc.jar $3
rm -rf temp tmpdeob.jar.BACKUP todeob.jar
}

deob ./rsCURRENT.jar ./rsCURRENT_DEOB_BIN.jar ./rsCURRENT_DEOB_SRC.jar

edit:
here is the running log, minus the jad output:

field = FIELD[fi.M.Z]
field = FIELD[client.jb.Z]

applying transform: ub-folder
applying transform: notremover
out = tmpdeob.jar

                      15, Rue de Clery Paris France

                      Loaded 284 classes

[2009.01.25 03:35:31] Saving 284 classes...
[2009.01.25 03:35:31] Terminating normally. See "/home/mopar/rsdev/rs/ZKM_log.txt" for more detail.

I also tried it on 520, which had 43 errors.

Anyone see a reason that should be happening?

edit: to make sure I didn’t do anything wrong, I downloaded ollie’s script and everything from here:
http://www.arcanum.in/public/runescape/deobfuscator.rar
and booted into windows to try it, same broken results…

edit:
I am either running this wrong (I don’t think so) or it doesn’t actually work. The deobber and zkm run without errors also. I have a feeling it is not finding the control field correctly, any ideas?

note: as funorb classes do not have a “main(String[] s)” it is hard to tell the main class, so set it in run.xml, it will default to that main class if the in-built system cannot find it.
